&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Haematology Department&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Biomedical Scientist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;(Band 5/6 depending upon experience / qualification) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our friendly team as a Biomedical Scientist in the Haematology Department at Kettering General Hospital. We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic HCPC registered BMS with experience of working in Haematology and Transfusion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 applications will be considered from individuals with HCPC registration and Bands 6 applicants will be required to have an IBMS Specialist Portfolio.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be required to actively participate in the out of hour’s service (weekend and night work) following completion of in-house training and competency assessment. Applicants will need to possess good communication skills and the ability to work as part of a team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Department is equipped with new analysers, Sysmex XN-9000, CS5100 and Bio-Rad IH-1000. The Laboratory is computerised with I-Soft Telepath system and EQMS quality management system. The department is accredited to UKAS ISO 15189 and is registered with the Institute of Biomedical Sciences as a training laboratory for pre and post registration training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Mike Silverstone&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Haematology Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address mike.silverstone@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536 492693&lt;/p&gt;
